In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates authority to the Director of the Office of Management and Budget under Public Law 117-169. The delegated authority relates to the certification of certain loan guarantees and projects. The President's authority to delegate such functions and authorities is derived from the Constitution and the laws of the United States, specifically section 301 of title 3, United States Code. The Director of the Office of Management and Budget is instructed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.